#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:4
msgid "IP assignment via DHCP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:6
msgid ""
"The Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) assigns computers an IP "
"address, the subnet mask and further settings for the gateway or NetBIOS "
"server as necessary. The IP address can be set fixed or dynamic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:10
msgid ""
"The use of DHCP allows central assignment and control of IP addresses via"
" the LDAP directory without performing manual configuration on the "
"individual computer systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:14
msgid "The DHCP integration in UCS only supports IPv4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:16
msgid ""
"In a *DHCP service*, DHCP servers are grouped in a shared LDAP "
"configuration. Global configuration parameters are entered in the DHCP "
"service; specific parameters in the subordinate objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:20
msgid ""
"A DHCP server can be installed from the Univention App Center with the "
"application :program:`DHCP server`. Alternatively, the software package "
":program:`univention-dhcp` can be installed. Additional information can "
"be found in :ref:`computers-softwaremanagement-install-software`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:25
msgid ""
"Every DHCP assigns IP addresses via DHCP. In the default setting, only "
"static IP addresses are assigned to computer objects registered in the "
"UCS LDAP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:28
msgid ""
"If only fixed IP addresses are assigned, as many DHCP servers as required"
" may be used in a DHCP service. All the DHCP servers procure identical "
"data from the LDAP and offer the DHCP clients the data multiple times. "
"DHCP clients then accept the first answer and ignore the rest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:33
msgid ""
"If dynamic IP addresses are also assigned, the DHCP failover mechanism "
"must be employed and a maximum of two DHCP servers can be used per "
"subnet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:36
msgid ""
"A *DHCP host* entry is used to make the DHCP service aware of a computer."
" A DHCP host object is required for computers attempting to retrieve a "
"fixed IP address over DHCP. DHCP computer objects do not normally need to"
" be created manually, because they are created automatically when a DHCP "
"service is assigned to a computer object with a fixed IP address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:42
msgid ""
"A *DHCP subnet* entry is required for every subnet, irrespective of "
"whether dynamic IP addresses are to be assigned from this subnet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:45
msgid ""
"Configuration parameters can be assigned to the different IP ranges by "
"creating *DHCP pools* within subnets. In this way unknown computers can "
"be allowed in one IP range and excluded from another IP range. DHCP pools"
" can only be created below DHCP subnet objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:50
msgid ""
"If several IP subnets are used in a physical Ethernet network, this "
"should be entered as a *DHCP shared subnet* below a *DHCP shared "
"network*. *DHCP shared subnet* objects can only be created below *DHCP "
"shared network* objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:54
msgid ""
"Values which are set on a DHCP configuration level always apply for this "
"level and all subordinate levels, unless other values are specified "
"there. Similar to policies, the value which is closest to the object "
"always applies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:61
msgid "Composition of the DHCP configuration via DHCP LDAP objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:63
msgid ""
"The left column of the UMC module :guilabel:`DHCP` includes a list of all"
" the DHCP services. To add an object to a DHCP service - for example in "
"an additional subnet - the corresponding service must be selected. "
":guilabel:`Add` is then used to create the object in this service. To "
"create a new DHCP service, start by selecting *All DHCP services*. "
"Clicking on :guilabel:`Add` then creates a new service. If an object is "
"saved within a service, the service is labeled in UMC dialogues as a "
"*superordinate object*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:74
msgid "Administration of DHCP services"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:76
msgid ""
"DHCP services are managed in the UMC module :guilabel:`DHCP` (see :ref"
":`central-user-interface`). To create a new DHCP service, *All DHCP "
"services* needs to be selected in the left column of the UMC module. "
"Clicking on :guilabel:`Add` then creates a new service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:81
msgid ""
"A DHCP server can only serve one DHCP service; to use another DHCP "
"service, a separate DHCP server must be set up (see :ref:`networks-dhcp-"
"dhcpserver`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:84
msgid ""
"The following parameters are often set on the DHCP service object which "
"then apply to all the computers which are served by this DHCP service "
"(unless other values are entered in lower levels):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:88
msgid "*Domain name* and *Domain name servers* under *Policy: DHCP DNS*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:90
msgid "*NetBIOS name servers* under *Policy: DHCP NetBIOS*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:92
msgid ""
"A description of this and the other DHCP policies can be found at :ref"
":`networks-dhcp-policies`."
msgstr ""

