#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:111
msgid "Administration of DHCP server entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:113
msgid ""
"Each server which should offer the DHCP service requires a *DHCP server* "
"entry in the LDAP directory. The entry does not normally need to be "
"created manually, instead it is created by the join script of the "
":program:`univention-dhcp` package. However, to create another record "
"manually, a DHCP service must be selected in the left column of the UMC "
"module :guilabel:`DHCP`. :menuselection:`Add --> DHCP Server` can then be"
" used to register a new server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:129
msgid "Server name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:130
msgid ""
"The computer name that the DHCP service should offer is entered in this "
"input field, e.g., ``ucs-primary``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:133
msgid ""
"A server can only ever provide a single DHCP service and therefore cannot"
" be entered in more than one DHCP service at the same time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:139
msgid "Administration of DHCP subnets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:141
msgid ""
"DHCP subnets are managed in the UMC module :guilabel:`DHCP` (see :ref"
":`central-user-interface`). To create another subnet, a DHCP service must"
" be selected in the left column. :menuselection:`Add --> DHCP: Subnet` "
"can be used to create a new subnet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:146
msgid ""
"A DHCP subnet entry is required for every subnet from which dynamic or "
"fixed IP addresses are to be assigned. It is only necessary to enter IP "
"address ranges if IP addresses are to be assigned dynamically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:150
msgid ""
"If *DHCP shared subnet* objects are to be used, the corresponding subnets"
" should be created below the *DHCP shared subnet* container created for "
"this purpose (see :ref:`networks-dhcp-shared-subnets`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:163
msgid "Subnet address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:164
msgid ""
"The IP address of the subnet must be entered in dot-decimal form in this "
"input field, e.g., ``192.0.2.0``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:167
msgid "Net mask"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:168
msgid ""
"The network mask can be entered in this input field as the network prefix"
" or in dot-decimal form. If the network mask is entered in dot-decimal "
"form it will be subsequently be converted into the corresponding network "
"prefix and later also shown so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:173
msgid "Dynamic address assignment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:174
msgid ""
"Here one can set up individual or multiple IP address ranges for dynamic "
"assignment. The range stretches from the *First address* to the *Last "
"address* in dot-decimal form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:180
msgid ""
"Dynamic IP ranges for a subnet should always either be specified "
"exclusively in the subnet entry or exclusively in one or more special "
"pool entries. The types of IP range entries within a subnet must not be "
"mixed! If different IP ranges with different configurations are be set up"
" in one subnet, pool entries must be created for this purpose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:186
msgid ""
"At this level, the gateway for all computers in a subnet is often set "
"using the *Policy: DHCP Routing* tab (unless other entries are performed "
"at lower levels)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:192
msgid "Administration of DHCP pools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:194
msgid ""
"DHCP pools can only be managed via the UMC module :guilabel:`LDAP "
"directory`. To do so, one must always be in a DHCP subnet object - a DHCP"
" pool object must always be created below a DHCP subnet object - and a "
"*DHCP: Pool* object added with :guilabel:`Add`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:199
msgid ""
"If DHCP pools are created in a subnet, no IP address range should be "
"defined in the subnet entry. These should only be specified via the pool "
"entries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:205
msgid "General tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:215 ../../ip-config/network-objects.rst:35
msgid "Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:216
msgid ""
"An unambiguous name for the DHCP pool must be entered in this input "
"field, e.g., ``testnet.compaby.example``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:219
msgid "Dynamic range"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:220
msgid ""
"Here you can enter the IP addresses in dot-decimal form that are to be "
"dynamically assigned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:226
msgid "Advanced settings tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:229
msgid "*Advanced settings* tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:236
msgid "Failover peer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:237
msgid ""
"The name of a failover configuration, which must to be configured "
"manually in file :file:`/etc/dhcp/local.conf`. Further information can be"
" found at `A Basic Guide to Configuring DHCP Failover <isc-dhcp-"
"failover_>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:242
msgid "Allow known clients"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:243
msgid ""
"A computer is identified by its MAC address. If this input field is set "
"to ``allow`` or unset, a computer **with** a matching DHCP host entry "
"(see :ref:`ip-config-dhcp-objects-hosts`) is eligible to receive an IP "
"address from this pool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:248 ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:257
msgid ""
"If set to ``deny``, the computer doesn't receive an IP address from the "
"pool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:251
msgid "Allow unknown clients"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:252
msgid ""
"A computer is identified by its MAC address. If this input field is set "
"to ``allow`` or unset, a computer **without** a matching DHCP host entry "
"(see :ref:`ip-config-dhcp-objects-hosts`) is eligible to receive an IP "
"address from this pool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:260
msgid "Allow dynamic BOOTP clients"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:261
msgid ""
"BOOTP is the predecessor of the DHCP protocol. It has no mechanism to "
"renew leases and by default assigns leases infinitely, which can deplete "
"the pool. If this options is set to ``allow`` clients can retrieve an IP "
"address from this pool using BOOTP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:266
msgid "All clients"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:267
msgid ""
"If this option is set to ``deny`` the pool is disabled globally. This is "
"only useful in exceptional scenarios."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:273
msgid "Registration of computers with DHCP computer objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:275
msgid ""
"A *DHCP host* entry is used to register the respective computer in the "
"DHCP service. Computers can be handled depending on their registration "
"status. Known computers may get fixed and dynamic IP addresses from the "
"DHCP service; unknown computers only get dynamic IP addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:280
msgid ""
"DHCP computer entries are usually created automatically when a computer "
"is added via the computer management. Below the DHCP service object you "
"have the possibility of adding DHCP computer entries or editing existing "
"entries manually, irrespective of whether they were created manually or "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:285
msgid ""
"DHCP host objects are managed in the UMC module :guilabel:`DHCP` (see "
":ref:`central-user-interface`). To register a host in the DHCP manually, "
"a DHCP service must be selected in the left column of the module. "
":menuselection:`Add --> DHCP: Host` can be used to register a host."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:299 ../../ip-config/dns.rst:369
msgid "Hostname"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:300
msgid ""
"A name for the computer is entered in this input field (which usually "
"also has an entry in the computer management). It is recommended to enter"
" the same name and the same MAC address for the computer in both entries "
"to facilitate assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:305
msgid "Type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:306
msgid ""
"The type of network used can be selected in this selection list. "
"*Ethernet* almost always needs to be selected here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:309 ../../ip-config/dns.rst:550
msgid "Address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:310
msgid ""
"The MAC address of the network card needs to be entered here, e.g., "
"``2e:44:56:3f:12:32`` or ``2e-44-56-3f-12-32``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:313
msgid "Fixed IP addresses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:314
msgid ""
"One or more fixed IP addresses can be assigned to the computer here. In "
"addition to an IP address, a fully qualified domain name can also be "
"entered, which is resolved into one or more IP addresses by the DHCP "
"server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:322
msgid "Management of DHCP shared networks / DHCP shared subnets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:324
msgid ""
"*DHCP shared network* objects accept subnets which use a common physical "
"network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:327
msgid ""
"DHCP shared network objects are managed in the UMC module "
":guilabel:`DHCP` (see :ref:`central-user-interface`). To create a shared "
"network, a DHCP service must be selected in the left column of the "
"module. :menuselection:`Add --> DHCP: Shared Network` can be used to "
"register a network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:334
msgid ""
"A shared network must contain at least one shared subnet object. "
"Otherwise the DHCP service will terminate itself and cannot be restarted "
"until the configuration is fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:347
msgid "Shared network name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:348
msgid "A name for the shared network must be entered in this input field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:350
msgid ""
"Subnets are declared as a *DHCP shared subnet* when they use the same, "
"common physical network. All subnets which use the same network must be "
"stored below the same shared network container. A separate *DHCP shared "
"subnet* object must be created for each subnet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:355
msgid ""
"DHCP shared subnet objects can only be managed via the UMC module "
":guilabel:`LDAP directory`. To do so, one must always be in a DHCP shared"
" network object - a DHCP shared subnet object must always be created "
"below a DHCP shared network object - and a *DHCP shared subnet* object "
"added with :guilabel:`Add`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:364
msgid "Configuration of clients via DHCP policies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:368
msgid ""
"Many of the settings for DHCP are configured via policies. They are also "
"applied to DHCP computer objects if a policy is linked to the LDAP base "
"or one of the other intermediate containers. As the settings for DHCP "
"computer objects have the highest priority, other settings for subnetwork"
" and service objects are ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:374
msgid ""
"For this reason, DHCP policies should be linked directly to the DHCP "
"network objects (e.g., the DHCP subnetworks)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:377
msgid ""
"Alternatively, the LDAP class ``univentionDhcpHost`` can be added in the "
"advanced settings of the policies under :menuselection:`Object --> "
"Excluded object classes`. Such policies are then no longer applied to the"
" DHCP computer objects, with the result that the settings from the DHCP "
"subnetwork and service are used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:385
msgid ""
"When using the command line :command:`udm dhcp/host list` (see also :ref"
":`central-udm-example-dnsdhcp`), it is possible to use the option "
"``--policies 0`` to display the effective settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:393
msgid "Setting the gateway"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:395
msgid ""
"The default gateway can be specified via DHCP with a *DHCP routing* "
"policy, which is managed in the UMC module :guilabel:`Policies` (see :ref"
":`central-policies`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:408
msgid "Routers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:409
msgid ""
"The names or IP addresses of the routers are to be entered here. It must "
"be verified that the DHCP server can resolve these names in IP addresses."
" The routers are contacted by the client in the order in which they stand"
" in the selection list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:417
msgid "Setting the DNS servers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:419
msgid ""
"The name servers to be used by a client can be specified via DHCP with a "
"*DHCP DNS* policy, which is managed in the UMC module "
":guilabel:`Policies` (see :ref:`central-policies`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:432
msgid "Domain name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:433
msgid ""
"The name of the domain, which the client automatically appends on "
"computer names that it sends to the DNS server for resolution and which "
"are not FQDNs. Usually this is the name of the domain to which the client"
" belongs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:438
msgid "Domain name servers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:439
msgid ""
"Here IP addresses or fully qualified domain names (FQDNs) of DNS servers "
"can be added. When using FQDNs, it must be verified that the DHCP server "
"can resolve the names in IP addresses. The DNS servers are contacted by "
"the clients according to the order specified here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:447
msgid "Setting the WINS server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:449
msgid ""
"The WINS server to be used can be specified via DHCP with a *DHCP "
"NetBIOS* policy, which is managed in the UMC module :guilabel:`Policies` "
"(see :ref:`central-policies`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:462
msgid "NetBIOS name servers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:463
msgid ""
"The names or IP addresses of the NetBIOS name servers (also known as WINS"
" servers) should be entered here. It must be verified that the DHCP "
"server can resolve these names in IP addresses. The servers entered are "
"contacted by the client in the order in which they stand in the selection"
" list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:469
msgid "NetBIOS scope"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:470
msgid ""
"The NetBIOS over TCP/IP scope for the client according to the "
"specification in :rfc:`1001` and :rfc:`1002`. Attention must be paid to "
"uppercase and lowercase when entering the NetBIOS scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:474
msgid "NetBIOS node type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:475
msgid "This field sets the node type of the client. Possible values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:477
msgid "``1 B-node`` (Broadcast: no WINS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:479
msgid "``2 P-node`` (Peer: only WINS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:481
msgid "``4 M-node`` (Mixed: first Broadcast, then WINS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:483
msgid "``8 H-node`` (Hybrid: first WINS, then Broadcast)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:488
msgid "Configuration of the DHCP lease"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:490
msgid ""
"The validity of an assigned IP address - a so-called DHCP lease - can be "
"specified with a *DHCP lease time* policy, which is managed in the UMC "
"module :guilabel:`Policies` (see :ref:`central-policies`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:503
msgid "Default lease time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:504
msgid ""
"If the client does not request a specific lease time, the standard lease "
"time is assigned. If this input field is left empty, the DHCP server's "
"default value is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:508
msgid "Maximum lease time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ip-config/dhcp.rst:509
msgid ""
"The maximum lease time specifies the longest period of time for which a "
"lease can be granted. If this input field is left empty, the DHCP "
"server's default value is used."
msgstr ""

